    <chapter>
      <heading>
        Software documentation for the TTIOAnonymizationPolicy
        class
      </heading>
      <class name="TTIOAnonymizationPolicy" super="NSObject">
        <declared>TTIOAnonymizer.h</declared>
        <desc>
          Milestone 28 — spectral anonymization. Applies
          caller-selected policies to a dataset and
          writes a new ``.tio`` file. The original is never
          modified. Supported policies: redactSAAVSpectra —
          remove spectra with SAAV identifications
          maskIntensityBelowQuantile — zero
          intensities below a percentile
          maskRareMetabolites — suppress
          rare-metabolite signals coarsenMzDecimals —
          reduce m/z precision coarsenChemicalShiftDecimals —
          reduce ppm precision (NMR) stripMetadataFields —
          remove operator/serial/source/timestamps Output
          carries the ``opt_anonymized`` feature flag and a
          ``ProvenanceRecord`` documenting which
          policies ran. API status: Stable. Cross-language
          equivalents: Python: ttio.anonymization Java:
          global.thalion.ttio.protection.Anonymizer
        </desc>
        <method type="NSInteger">
          <sel>coarsenChemicalShiftDecimals</sel>
          <desc>
            Getter for property 'coarsenChemicalShiftDecimals'
            with attributes (nonatomic, readwrite, assign). See
            also
            <ref type="method" id="-setCoarsenChemicalShiftDecimals:" class="TTIOAnonymizationPolicy">[TTIOAnonymizationPolicy -setCoarsenChemicalShiftDecimals:]</ref>
          </desc>
        </method>
        <method type="NSInteger">
          <sel>coarsenMzDecimals</sel>
          <desc>
            Getter for property 'coarsenMzDecimals' with
            attributes (nonatomic, readwrite, assign). See
            also
            <ref type="method" id="-setCoarsenMzDecimals:" class="TTIOAnonymizationPolicy">[TTIOAnonymizationPolicy -setCoarsenMzDecimals:]</ref>
          </desc>
        </method>
        <method type="double">
          <sel>maskIntensityBelowQuantile</sel>
          <desc>
            Getter for property 'maskIntensityBelowQuantile'
            with attributes (nonatomic, readwrite, assign). See
            also
            <ref type="method" id="-setMaskIntensityBelowQuantile:" class="TTIOAnonymizationPolicy">[TTIOAnonymizationPolicy -setMaskIntensityBelowQuantile:]</ref>
          </desc>
        </method>
        <method type="BOOL">
          <sel>maskRareMetabolites</sel>
          <desc>
            Getter for property 'maskRareMetabolites' with
            attributes (nonatomic, readwrite, assign). See
            also
            <ref type="method" id="-setMaskRareMetabolites:" class="TTIOAnonymizationPolicy">[TTIOAnonymizationPolicy -setMaskRareMetabolites:]</ref>
          </desc>
        </method>
        <method type="NSArray*">
          <sel>maskRegions</sel>
          <desc>
            Getter for property 'maskRegions' with attributes
            (readwrite, nonatomic, copy). See also
            <ref type="method" id="-setMaskRegions:" class="TTIOAnonymizationPolicy">[TTIOAnonymizationPolicy -setMaskRegions:]</ref> A list of (chromosome, start, end) tuples; any read whose mapping position falls in any region has its sequence and qualities bytes zeroed (kept in the index so downstream tooling iterating by index still sees N reads). Each entry is an NSArray of three elements: NSString chr, NSNumber start (int64), NSNumber end (int64). <code>nil</code> means "no regions to mask".
          </desc>
        </method>
        <method type="BOOL">
          <sel>randomiseQualities</sel>
          <desc>
            Getter for property 'randomiseQualities' with
            attributes (nonatomic, readwrite, assign). See
            also
            <ref type="method" id="-setRandomiseQualities:" class="TTIOAnonymizationPolicy">[TTIOAnonymizationPolicy -setRandomiseQualities:]</ref> Replace every per-base Phred quality score with a single caller-specified constant (default 30). The "randomise" name matches the M90 spec language; the actual replacement is deterministic per-read so anonymised.tio files stay reproducible.
          </desc>
        </method>
        <method type="uint8_t">
          <sel>randomiseQualitiesConstant</sel>
          <desc>
            Getter for property 'randomiseQualitiesConstant'
            with attributes (nonatomic, readwrite, assign). See
            also
            <ref type="method" id="-setRandomiseQualitiesConstant:" class="TTIOAnonymizationPolicy">[TTIOAnonymizationPolicy -setRandomiseQualitiesConstant:]</ref> The per-base byte (Phred score) substituted in by randomiseQualities. Defaults to 30.
          </desc>
        </method>
        <method type="NSDictionary*">
